I"ï<h1 id="conductance">Conductance</h1>

<p>Conductance $(G)$ is simply the reciprocal of resistance $(R)$. Conductance can be easily calculated by getting the inverse of resistance.</p>
<p align="center" style="background-color:rgba(64, 130, 110, 0.07);
border: 3px solid rgba(64, 130, 110, 0.9);
border-radius:7px;
padding:10px;
margin:5px;">
    $$\begin{align}
        G = \frac{1}{R} = \frac{A}{\rho L}
        \label{eq:conductance using resistivity length and area}
    \end{align}$$
</p>

